<font color="#FF0000">CAUSES NOT SYMPTOMS</font><br>
<tt>Fri Jan  9 14:37:17 US/Eastern 1998
</tt><p>
I would like yours and other's reviews and comments on the following post.  I, too, am searching!<br><br>
Part of my &quot;keep it simple, Stupid&quot; philosophy tells me that governments are nothing more than large groups of people that cling together around some common belief(s).  God is perceived by many as the most powerful force.  Fear generates from the thoughts that one does not please God in their religious views and practices unless they subscribe to a certain set of rules and procedures.  People who do not agree are considered as threats.  Those who depart from tradition erode that sense of security found in religion and the stage for disagreement is set.  Hundreds of thousands<br>
of Native Americans perished in the name of God to satisfy ungodly motives to steal land and murder indigenous people.  Religions are the most fanatical forms of government.  Why?  Because the true intent of a benevolent God is twisted to satisfy the greed and superstitions of man.  How many staunch Christians, Jews, Moslems etc. are you aware of that select and manipulate the scriptures of their faith to achieve worldly goals?  Many religions are based upon the truth of tenacity, something is true simply because I believe it to be true, the truth of authority, something is true because a person in power told me so, or the truth of A Priori, it is true because of a gut feeling.  I chose to believe that God is perfect and religions are often lacking!  Still they are forms of government.<br>
The Communist Manifesto, drafted and written by Marx and Engels, was a plan to help the tide of rural workers who came to the factories at the beginning of the industrial revolution.  Not unlike labor unions, the intent was good..to protect the workers.  It appears to me that any good plan is only as good as the leadership that implements it and the people that make up the body.  Greed, a child of insecurity, always appears as a &quot;fly in the soup!&quot;<br>
Insecurity is the culprit.  Napoleon was a small man with a pathologically small penis who devoted his thinking to acquisition of power and orchestrated the deaths of many people to &quot;prove his manhood.&quot;  Poverty, low socio-economic status, is certainly a threat to a healthy sense of security.  Thus hundreds of thousands braved the frontiers of North America to find wealth by killing, cheating and stealing... it was the American way!  The railroads exemplify the use of the insecure masses to satisfy the gluttony of a powerful few.  Not unlike the Crusades or Vietnam.<br>
One is foolish to believe that the Civil War was fought to free the slaves.  It was pure economics, an ugly necessity that imprisons all men.  Indoctrinated young men, often perplexed and insecure as they stand on the threshold of manhood are easily swayed to take up justifiable causes to effect the unjustifiable for a controlling few.<br>
All governments are simply a collection of people.  It seems insane to advocate the virtues of different types of governments as a solution to man's dilemma.  Any government would work for any person if the principles of truth, love and justice prevailed above lies, hatred, and injustice.<br>
Our governments are not improved by replacing Kings, Dictators, and Presidents.  Our governments are improved by replacing hunger with food, ignorance with insight, immorality with morals, greed with charity, and laziness with a good work ethic. How do you do that?  Simple!  Give children the essential comforts, defined boundaries, love and affection and security that lead to a self actualization of humane endeavor.  It is done most effectively by example from significant others...heros and not cowards, contractual commitment to strong marriages that provide strong homes..not single parent operations, efforts to maintain physical fitness rather than to slip into sloven obesity and absence of musculature and maintain a true but personal communion with God.<br>
Keep it simple, Stupid!  Don't treat symptoms...treat causes!<br><br>
Mustang Two Four
